summary: NY Line Store After Animefest me and my sister decided to stop by the Line store before we took the train home. I really wanted...
caption:
NY Line Store

After Animefest me and my sister decided to stop by the Line store before we took the train home. I really wanted to go get taoyaki from Korea Town but my sister was too tired to walk all the way there so we agreed on the Line store instead. The store was crowded due to the Citi Concert being the next day. We walked right in and the security guard opened the door for us. It was weird to see a security guard at the door but then we realized that there was a long line in order to get into the store, It literally went down 3 blocks in Times Square. Since the security guard didn’t say anything we just kept it going. I felt bad but if God and the security guard permitted us to get in, then Ima stay right here. We weren’t going to stay long or have a shopping spree since we came prior to that day to buy what we wanted already. The Bt21 merch ain’t cheap either and I already spent what I needed to spend for the day at Animefest so I only took pictures of the chaos and bought one kooky key chain. As we were waiting in line inside the store, girls were going crazy and grabbing a lot of the huge plushies of the bt21 characters, employees of the store were yelling “who wants a chimmy headband!!” while they opened a shipment package of headbands for screaming fans saying “over here!!, I want one!!”, and loads of fans were raging over getting everything the store had to offer. It was truly insane and fan girls were cleaning out the shelves of plushies, sandals, sweaters, stationary, and employees had to restock constantly. 

Its crazy to see the impact BTS has on fans. Fans are willing to spend hundreds on concert tickets, hundreds on hotels and flights (if their from another country) and then another hundreds on merch in the line store and at the concert. Then again, if you have the money, why not? I guess I am part of it for being there…but my ass will never be of the level of fangirl I saw that day. Those girls were dedicated to the core.
